* (1) (Amended, SG No. 35/2011, effective 3.05.2011) The activities for implementation of the state policy for promotion energy end-use efficiency and provision of energy services shall be implemented by the Executive Director of the Agency for Sustainable Energy Development, hereinafter referred to as "the Agency".
* (Amended, SG No. 59/2013, effective 5.07.2013) The Executive Director of the Agency shall be appointed and removed by the Minister of Economy and Energy in consultation with the Prime Minister.
* The Executive Director:
* shall direct, manage and represent the Agency;
* shall exercise control in the cases provided for by the law;
* shall participate in the development of national energy efficiency action plans;
* shall organise the implementation of activities and measures included in the national energy efficiency action plans;
* (amended, SG No. 59/2013, effective 5.07.2013) shall submit annually to the Minister of Economy and Energy a report on the implementation of the national energy efficiency action plans;
* shall confirm the amount of energy savings achieved as a result of the energy services rendered, by issuing energy savings certificates and by other energy efficiency improvement measures;
* shall participate in the elaboration of drafts of statutory instruments in the sphere of energy efficiency;
* shall organise the drawing up of model contracts for provision of energy services, intended to use various financial instruments by the purchasers of energy services and to implement other energy efficiency improvement activities and measures;
* shall organise the elaboration of projects and shall conclude voluntary agreements;
* shall perform monitoring of the voluntary agreements;
* shall interact with the bodies of state power and with the local self-government authorities, with employer associations, with branch organisations, with consumer associations and with not-for-profit legal entities for the implementation of the energy efficiency improvement activities and measures;
* shall organise the creation and maintenance of a national information system on the state of energy efficiency;
* (amended, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) shall organise the creation and maintenance of the public registers referred to in Article 23a Paragraph (1) and Article 34a Paragraph (1);
* shall provide assistance to the bodies of state power and to the local self-government authorities, as well as to the participants in the market for energy services, in the fulfilment of their obligations under this Act;
* shall organise the promotion of energy efficiency improvement activities and measures;
* s hall facilitate the development of training in energy efficiency;
* (amended, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) shall organise the creation and maintenance of a list of buildings, industrial systems, hot water boiler heating systems and air-conditioning systems which must be brought into conformity with energy efficiency requirements;
* (new, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) shall participate in the development of methodologies for evaluation of energy savings;

