* (1) (Amended, SG No. 35/2011, effective 3.05.2011, SG No. 15/2013, effective 1.01.2014, SG No. 59/2013, effective 5.07.2013) The Agency for Sustainable Energy Development shall be a public-financed legal person, with a head office in Sofia, and shall enjoy the status of an executive agency under the Minister of Economy and Energy.
* For the implementation of its activities, the Agency shall set up territorial units in the regions referred to in Article 4 (3) of the Regional Development Act. The headquarters of the territorial units shall be determined by the Rules of Organisation referred to in Paragraph (3).
* The activities, structure and work organisation of the Agency shall be determined by Rules of Organisation adopted by the Council of Ministers.
* (Amended, SG No. 35/2011, effective 3.05.2011) The Agency for Sustainable Energy Development administers the proceeds from:
* (amended, SG No. 15/2013, effective 1.01.2014) state budget subsidies;
* own activities;
* proceeds from fines and pecuniary penalties imposed by penalty decrees issued in the course of implementation of control according to the procedure established by this Act;
* international programmes and agreements;
* other sources determined by a statutory instrument of the Council of Ministers.
* (Repealed, SG No. 15/2013, effective 1.01.2014).
* (Repealed, SG No. 38/2012, effective 1.07.2012).
* (Repealed, SG No. 38/2012, effective 1.07.2012).

The National Energy Efficiency Strategy shall define:
* the state policy priorities and the long-term energy savings targets for achieving competitiveness of the national economy;
* (amended, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) the national targets and the means for the achievement thereof;
* (amended, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) the guidelines for achievement of the national targets, as well as the mechanisms, incentives and institutional, financial and legal frameworks to remove existing market barriers and imperfections that impede the efficient end use of energy;
* the guidelines for creation of favourable conditions for the development and promotion of the market for energy services and for the delivery of other energy efficiency improvement measures to final consumers.

developed on the basis of the National Strategy referred to in Article 7 and shall contain:
* an analysis and evaluation of the implementation of the preceding national action plan;
* the national energy savings target, including the national intermediate indicative energy savings target;
* the individual energy savings targets, including the individual intermediate indicative energy savings targets
* energy efficiency improvement activities and measures planned for implementation;
* the obligations of the bodies of state power and the local self-government authorities in relation with the implementation of the measures planned;
* th e deadlines for implementation;
* the sources of financing, as well as a list of financial mechanisms and schemes for promotion of energy efficiency in buildings;
* the indicators for reporting the results achieved, as well as other necessary data.
* (Amended, SG No. 59/2013, effective 5.07.2013) The Executive Director of the Agency shall submit to the Minister of Economy and Energy the report referred to in Item 5 of Article 5 (3) by the 30th day of April of the year following the reporting year.
* (Amended, SG No. 59/2013, effective 5.07.2013) Not later than the 31st day of May of the respective year, the Minister of Economy and Energy shall lay the report referred to in Paragraph (2) before the Council of Ministers for adoption.

(New, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) The national plan for increasing the number of nearly zero energy buildings under Article 4a, item 3 shall contain:
* the national definition and technical parameters of nearly zero energy buildings, which shall reflect the domestic conditions;
* the term of operation of the plan;
* the national targets for increasing the number of nearly zero energy buildings depending on the classification of the types of buildings according to the Ordinance under Article 15, Paragraph 3;
* the policies and mechanisms, including financial ones, for promotion of construction of the buildings under item 3.

(Amended, SG No. 35/2011, effective 3.05.2011, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) (1) The national energy savings targets and the national intermediate indicative energy savings targets shall be allocated as individual energy savings targets and individual intermediate indicative energy savings targets with the action plans under Article 8 among:
* the retail energy sales companies;
* the owners of buildings referred to in Article 19;

Energy efficiency improvement activities shall be the activities associated with:
* (amended, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) energy efficiency certification of new buildings;
* (amended, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) energy efficiency audit and certification of buildings in use;
* energy audit of industrial systems;
* (amended, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) inspection of the energy efficiency of hot water boiler heating systems and air-conditioning systems in buildings;

Energy efficiency improvement activities shall be the activities associated with:
* (amended, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) energy efficiency certification of new buildings;
* (amended, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) energy efficiency audit and certification of buildings in use;
* energy audit of industrial systems;
* (amended, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) inspection of the energy efficiency of hot water boiler heating systems and air-conditioning systems in buildings;
* energy efficiency management;
* (new, SG No. 24/2013, effective 12.03.2013) improvement of energy performance of outdoor lighting Ð¦ street, park and other types.

have the necessary personnel -energy efficiency consultants who:
* have higher technical education acquired in the Republic of Bulgaria or in another Member State of the European Union, or in another state -Contracting Party to the Agreement on the European Economic Area, or in the Swiss Confederation;
* have acquired length of service in the relevant area -not less than two years for persons with a master's degree, and not less than three years -for persons with a bachelor's degree.

priority funding of projects for:
* implementation of measures for increasing energy efficiency of ultimate consumption of energy;
* use of energy from renewable sources in ultimate consumption of energy;

a representative of the Ministry of Environment and Water, designated by the Minister of Environment and Water;
* (new, SG No. 35/2011, effective 3.05.2011, amended, SG No. 66/2013, effective 26.07.2013) a representative of the Ministry of Regional Development, designated by the Minister of Regional Development;
* a representative of non-government organisations, the activities of which are focused on reducing the risk of global climate changes;
* two experts with higher economic education with experience in funding of projects in the area of power generation;
* an expert in the field of energy efficiency with higher engineering education;
* an expert in the field of renewable sources with higher engineering education.
